deck: Comic Book editor and short film writer/director.
description:
Formally Vertigo's rising star editor. Many of the most acclaimed Vertigo books from 2004 to 2010 were edited by Pornsak Pichetshote, cult favorites such as Seaguy and WE3 from Grant Morrison, to Vertigo's hottest books in 2010 like Sweet Tooth and Unwritten.

Because of the "restructuring" that DC faced when Paul Levitz stepped down as president, Vertigo has been unstable. In late September it was announced that Vertigo would be laying off some editors and Pornsak Pichetshote became causality to the "restructuring".

It is reported that Pornsak Pichetshote is still employed at DC looking over other aspects of the company.

Outside of Comic Books Pornsak Pichetshote has directed two short films: Women Who Eat Meat (2002) and Color of a Doubt: An Urban Fable (2005)
name: Pornsak Pichetshote

deck: An American comic book artist.
description:
Personal Life

Dustin Weaver as born in in San Diego, California, on the 3rd of October 1978, but grew up in Eagle River, Alaska. He currently live in Portland, Oregon. He is currently living with his fiancee, Lauren Fitzgerald, and their "freaking amazing" child, Lucy Fitzgerald Weaver who was born on August 11 2009. He has been described as fun loving person and being a really nice guy.

Career

Dustin has been a professional comic book artist since 2003. He's drawn different Star Wars titles at Dark Horse Comics, most notably Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic, and he drew the comic adoption of King Kong. After leaving Dark Horse he went to Marvel and is currently signed on with a exclusive contract with them. He has drawn several X-men stories, the first S.H.I.E.L.D. 6 issue mini series and is now working on the second S.H.I.E.L.D. mini-series. He is part of Periscope Studio, a collective of cartoonists, illustrators, writers, concept designers, graphic novelists, and storyboard artists based in downtown Portland, Oregon.
name: Dustin Weaver

deck: Creator of Scud, the Disposable Assassin.
description:
Born in Mayville Wisconsin, November 12th, 1969. Rob Schrab grow up in a small farm town, he was quite known for his ability to draw "as early as pre-school."
Â 
In 1998, Rob attended The Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design. While he was going to the Institute he meet his long-term friend Dan Harmon (who later became his writing partner).
Â 
In 1993, Rob drew the first issue of Scud the Disposable Assassin on his kitchen table. The comic book series went up to 24 issues. Two video games and action figure were based off the series and had three spin-offs.
Â 
Rob Schrab career continues on into Movies, TV and Comics. He now "lives in Los Angeles with his wonderful soul mate, Kate Freund and their baby Teddy-Bear, Diamond."
name: Rob Schrab

deck: Writer of the Discworld graphic novels.
description:
Better recognised for his novels than his graphic novels, having sold over 50,000,000 books, most of which were his Discworld novels. His first graphic novel was 'The Color of Magic' and he has done three more since then. He has hinted towards completing more in the near future.

Living in Sailsbury, Wiltshire with his wife Lyn and daughter Rhianna (also a writer) he spends most of his time playing 'intelligent' video games such as Half Life. In 2007 it was diagnosed that he had suffered a minor stroke in 2004/5. He currently has an Order of the British Empire (OBE) for services to literature. He takes influence from other cultural references to parody, such as Lenord de Quirm (Leonardo da Vinci), Cohen the Barbarian (Conan the Barbarian) and Hide Park (Hyde Park). He says that he doesn't want to get a life, because he feels like he's leading three already.
name: Terry Pratchett
